&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Insider is hiring a Cloud Engineer III to join our Cloud Engineering team dedicated to building and supporting scalable, secure and resilient infrastructure in AWS and other cloud providers.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Business Insider is for people who are driven, optimistic and always looking forward. Our mission is to inspire action through thought-provoking stories. We tell our audience what they want and need to know to improve their lives and the world with storytelling that is accessible, smart, sometimes unexpected, and always helpful. Our team members embody and uphold Business Insider’s three core values: we are all one team, we are effective, and we get better every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Cloud Engineering team is one of collaboration, innovation, and continuous improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role &amp;amp; Team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Cloud Engineer, you will contribute to the design, implementation, and optimisation of our cloud infrastructure, playing a pivotal role in the ongoing success of our tech teams, our writers and editors and the readership of the largest business news site in the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure the effectiveness of our DevOps culture, troubleshoot application and system issues and add minimal complexity to monitor, deploy and scale our continuously growing environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role reports directly to the Director of Cloud Engineering and sits on the Cloud Engineering Team. This role will be based in Belfast and offers an in office or work from home / hybrid opportunity.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate on the design and implementation of scalable and secure cloud infrastructure solutions on AWS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing and enhancing our global AWS services and infrastructure, adhering to security best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working closely with cross-functional teams to foster an effective DevOps culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshooting application and system issues in collaboration with feature team engineers, communicating status to the broader team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implementing minimal complexity to monitor, deploy, and scale a continuously growing environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ideal Candidate Has:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrable knowledge of building and supporting cloud applications at scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A positive attitude and ability to contribute effectively to discussions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional experience with AWS and Elastic Kubernetes Service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A high degree of comfort in deploying cloud native applications using Terraform and Kubernetes and the ability to evaluate emerging technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in coding in a modern programming language.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with DevOps practices and tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary &amp;amp; Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Market leading salary (dependent on skills, experience, and competencies)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hybrid flexible working - our amazing City Centre office or your home, the choice is yours.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;25 days annual leave + Bank Holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unrivalled culture and working environment with regular socials and company events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Private Medical Insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health cash plan&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;

&lt;p&gt;Role &amp;amp; Team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Business Insider is seeking an accomplished correspondent to join our award-winning enterprise team and produce impactful stories that readers can&#39;t find anywhere else.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Business Insider has long prioritized in-depth, revelatory journalism. You will collaborate closely with editors and reporters across our global newsroom to develop and execute some of Business Insider&#39;s most ambitious journalism, diving deep into the worlds of business, technology and innovation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of a team that has produced projects such as&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.businessinsider.com/ai-data-center-development-true-cost-environmental-impact-2025-6&quot;&gt; The True Cost of Data Centers&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.businessinsider.com/c-sections-hospitals-profit-business-cost-2025-8&quot;&gt; The Business of C-Sections&lt;/a&gt;, and an&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.businessinsider.com/lil-wayne-chris-brown-covid-relief-funds-svog-grant-2024-12&quot;&gt; investigation&lt;/a&gt; that revealed how celebrity musicians received millions of dollars from a pandemic-relief program, prompting a federal investigation and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.businessinsider.com/svog-restaurant-pandemic-fraud-prosecution-extension-passes-senate-2026-4&quot;&gt;new legislation&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You are someone with a track record in business journalism and are excited to do both quicker-turn enterprise stories and longer-term projects. Success is doing talk-of-the-town work that has impact.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is union-eligible and is based in New York City or San Francisco, with an in-office expectation of three days a week. It reports to our Executive Editor for Enterprise, Jennifer Maloney. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;All reporters at Business Insider have the opportunity to publish work and collaborate on joint investigations across the Axel Springer Global Reporters Network, which includes POLITICO, WELT, and BILD.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce revelatory journalism in the worlds of business, technology, and innovation with the aim of breaking stories that drive real-world consequences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify ambitious reporting targets&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Juggle long-term and short-turn efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cultivate and maintain a network of sources, and source up fast in new areas as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the graphics, photo, video, audience development teams to engage our audience and maximize our impact&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate has:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 10 years of experience in business or tech journalism, including a proven track record with investigative or enterprise work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of the business and tech worlds and the ability to explain complicated issues clearly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven ability to deliver complicated, sensitive stories and handle anonymous sourcing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using data sets, documents, or open-source reporting techniques such as social media tracking, geolocation, or satellite imagery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong storytelling instincts and excellent communication and organizational skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collegial approach to collaboration and a willingness to experiment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A commitment to journalistic excellence and integrity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary &amp;amp; Benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary: $110,000 - $150,000&amp;nbsp; (dependent on skills, experience, and competencies)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unlimited PTO, 10 paid holidays, and 16 weeks of parental leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive medical, dental, and vision insurance plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Matched and vested 401k plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;

&lt;p&gt;Business Insider is seeking a Leadership and Management chief correspondent to write about the people leading people, what they’re getting right, where they’re stumbling, and what our audience can learn from these actions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate has the ambition and authority to be an agenda-setting voice. This writer will have a wide view of the most-interesting developments in leadership in the news, and will have smart things to say about them on a frequent basis. We aren’t looking for an opinion writer but rather a person who will draw from years of reporting experience and constant fresh reporting to offer authoritative takes. Scoops are always welcome, insights expected.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a chief correspondent, this person is a “go anywhere” journalist working across platforms, meaning they have the opportunity to represent BI at live events, in the broader media, on our web site, newsletters, and more. In addition to having a regular byline on the site, this correspondent will experiment with new formats and reach audiences wherever they are.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is based in our New York City HQ with an in-office requirement of three days a week, and is union-eligible. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pitch and write original pieces on leadership and management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Get scoops that make Business Insider a must-read destination&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep a deep Rolodex of business leaders to access the best insights possible about management strategies and moves.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Constantly engage with sources, attend industry conferences, and stay ahead of emerging leadership trends.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with teams like video, live events, newsletters, and creative to deliver leadership and management coverage in new formats to new audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ideal Candidate Has:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep sourcing among executives and managers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 15 years of experience in business journalism covering leadership and workplace transformations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of breaking exclusive news and providing thought-provoking, analytical reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong writing ability featuring quick, accurate, and conversational copy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently, manage deadlines, and be flexible with new ideas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to excel at live journalism and across media broadly.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary &amp;amp; Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Base salary: $180,000 (dependent on skills, experience, and competencies)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unlimited PTO, 10 paid holidays, and 16 weeks of parental leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive medical, dental, and vision insurance plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Matched and vested 401k plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to resources for financial planning guidance, family planning services, mental health reach out and Employee Assistance Programs (EAP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additional benefits include commuter benefits, phone reimbursement, gym membership discounts, and more&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
