&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Insider is hiring a Staff Product Manager to join our Product Team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Business Insider is for people who are driven, optimistic and always looking forward. Our mission is to inspire action through thought-provoking stories. We tell our audience what they want and need to know to improve their lives and the world with storytelling that is accessible, smart, sometimes unexpected, and always helpful. Our team members embody and uphold Business Insider’s three core values: we are all one team, we are effective, and we get better every day.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Our Product Team exists to maximize the impact of our journalism by building products that move the company from a reach-based model toward deeper engagement and loyalty. We are a collaborative, inclusive, and impact-driven group that values outcomes over output, clear ownership, and thoughtful execution. Working in close partnership with engineering and technology, we bring together stakeholders across the company to prioritize and deliver meaningful work—creating essential, high-quality experiences that foster direct relationships with our audience and support long-term growth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;As Staff Product Manager, Monetization, you will lead the strategic direction for Business Insider’s monetized product ecosystem across subscriptions, advertising, and hybrid revenue models. You will own a core product domain with deep expertise, balancing tactical execution with long-term strategic vision to ensure monetization strengthens audience value, trust, and business growth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;You will partner closely with engineering, design, analytics, subscriptions, revenue, editorial, marketing, and business development to define the roadmap, shape investment priorities, and drive high-impact initiatives across the monetization portfolio. You will also play a key role in improving product development processes, mentoring product managers, and helping the broader organization make better decisions through clear strategy, strong judgment, and effective communication.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;This role reports to the VP, Product, and is based in our New York City HQ with a periodic in-office presence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Lead product strategy and execution across Business Insider’s monetization portfolio, with a strong emphasis on subscription growth, engagement, retention, and renewals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Own the long-term vision, roadmap, and success metrics for a core monetization domain, ensuring product investments align with company goals and customer needs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Identify opportunities to improve the subscriber experience across the lifecycle, using research, experimentation, and data to inform priorities and validate impact.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Partner with cross-functional teams to launch and iterate on products that drive conversion, reduce churn, deepen loyalty, and create sustainable revenue growth.&lt;/span

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Insider is hiring a weekend reporting fellow to cover trending business and tech news. The fellow would join a team covering the most compelling and impactful stories of the day on topics like &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.businessinsider.com/economy&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;the economy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.businessinsider.com/careers&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;the workplace&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;, and &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.businessinsider.com/artificial-intelligence&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Business Insider is for people who are driven, optimistic, and always looking ahead. Our mission is to inspire action through thought-provoking stories. We tell our audience what they want and need to know to improve their lives and the world with storytelling that is accessible, smart, sometimes unexpected, and always helpful. Our team members embody and uphold Business Insider’s three core values: We are all one team, we are effective, and we strive to get better every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.insider-inc.com/careers/fellowship-program&quot;&gt;Business Insider Fellowship Program&lt;/a&gt; is for early-career journalists who want to spend six months learning from a newsroom full of passionate, dedicated journalists. Fellows are assigned to teams and become experts in digital storytelling. They produce real work that is distributed to our audience of millions, and by the end of six months, they are prepared for the next phase of their journalism careers. This paid role requires you to work for 40 hours a week. Fellowships are typically hybrid. We expect New York-based fellows to come into our offices at least twice a week. Remote roles would be considered for exceptional candidates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role &amp;amp; Team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The fellow would write news stories about the impact that technology, corporations, and the economy are having on workers and the average person, like how AI is upending the workforce, how data centers are affecting local communities, how inflation is making groceries less affordable, or how the closure of the Strait of Hormuz is affecting the prices of gas and plane tickets. Fellows may also write about business personalities, consumer trends, real estate, AI, and other innovations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will spend their time doing meaningful work: researching, writing, pitching, and interviewing — and regular fast-turnaround original reporting. Reporters may also pitch travel assignments, though travel is not required as a condition of employment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role requires working a Wednesday-Sunday schedule&lt;/strong&gt; and reports to our Senior Weekend Editor on the Business News team.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Taking assignments from editors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pitching story ideas, including original reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sourcing up on assigned beats&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Researching and conducting interviews&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Covering breaking news&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Updating existing coverage with new developments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ideal candidate has:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An interest in covering the most compelling news from the world’s biggest companies — and the rivalries and controversies that can result&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A keen eye for impactful and potentially market-moving corporate news and how employees are reacting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A broad knowledge base spanning multiple industries and company types&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A fundamental understanding of how corporations conduct business and grow&lt;/li&gt;
